<para>Description: <linebreak/>
 This node allows the robot to reach a position with a given orientation. Firstly it orients the robot in the direction of the goal and moves towards it. Once the robot has reached the correct x and y coordinates it rotates to reach the correct orientation. The velocities, both angular and linear are set by the node user_interface and are received on the topic /vel. If the goal is set cancelled by the client of the action server then the velocities are all set to zero and the action server is set preempted. </para>
